(firstQuint)Relationship Between Erythropoietin Administration and Stress Responses in Trauma Patients.

 Transfusion of blood products has many disadvantages.

 Erythropoietin is used to increase red blood cells production and decrease such disadvantages.

In some studies anti inflammatory effects is shown for Erythropoietin.

 One of the most problems in the intensive care unit is stress response.

 we are going to evaluate effects of erythropoietin on oxidative stress and inflammation in trauma patient in intensive care unit.

